<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-06-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-06-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="187" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d187">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Sherman</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">White</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-06-21"><hi rend="italic">June 21,
                                1897</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 20.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to inform you that Mr. Uhl’s
                            dispatch No. 372, of the 3d instant, reporting that he had made further
                            intervention on behalf of Mr. Alfred Meyer, has been received.</p>
                        <p>The Department fully approves Mr. Uhl’s course in regard to the matter,
                            and would be glad to have you keep this case in mind in view of the
                            importance of the principle involved.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully, yours,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Sherman.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>